  "title": "*feature* option to show all refinementList options even when count is 0 if less than limit",
  "body": "**Feature: What is your use case for such a feature?**\r\nWe have a location preference facet with options NY, SF, Remote. We want all three of these to always be visible as choices (like a menu) but allow the user to select multiple like the refinementList\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your proposed API entry? The new option to add? What is the behavior?**\r\nadd showEmptyValues: [boolean] on refinementList OR multiselect: [boolean] on menu\r\n\r\nA quick test made this seem impossible using the widgets as is, or using a connector.\r\n\r\nattempted to use a connector, but RefinementListRenderingOptions.items doesnt contain refinements with a count of 0\r\n\r\nA custom widget may be an option, but was looking for a simpler solution",
